| 2004 || {{dts|December 17}} || Detention capacity || Update || DHS (ICE) || The {{w|Intelligence Reform and Terrorism Prevention Act}} of 2004 directs DHS to increase by 8,000 in each of the Fiscal Years from 2005 to 2010 the number of beds available for immigration detention and removal operations of DHS. It also requires priority for the use of these additional beds to the detention of individuals charged with removability or inadmissibility on security and related grounds.<ref name=bed-quota-timeline>{{cite web|url = https://immigrantjustice.org/sites/default/files/content-type/issue/documents/2017-01/Immigration%20Detention%20Bed%20Quota%20Timeline%202017_01_05.pdf|title = Immigration Detention Bed Quota Timeline|date = January 1, 2017|accessdate = April 30, 2021}}</ref><ref name=irtpa-fulltext>{{cite web|url = https://www.congress.gov/bill/108th-congress/senate-bill/2845|title = S.2845 - Intelligence Reform and Terrorism Prevention Act of 2004|date = September 23, 2004|accessdate = April 30, 2021}}</ref>
