| 2021 || {{dts|December 16}} || Detention policy (family detention) || ICE || The Biden administration announces an end to family detention for the time being. Both Dilley and Karnes are converted to adult detention centers.<ref>{{cite web|url = https://www.axios.com/biden-ends-migrant-family-detention-border-immigration-b39f3e04-689a-486b-82de-7deb9412cea6.html|title = Scoop: Biden to stop holding undocumented families in detention centers|last = Knight|first = Stef|date = December 16, 2021|accessdate = December 18, 2021|publisher = Axios}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url = https://www.latimes.com/politics/story/2021-12-17/adults-only-biden-administration-repurposes-immigrant-family-detention-centers|title = Biden administration halts immigrant family detention for now|publisher = Los Angeles Times|date = December 17, 2021|accessdate = December 18, 2021}}</ref> || Texas || South Texas Family Residential Center, Dilley; Karnes Family Residential Center, Karnes City, Karnes County
